PASS	Passenger in the seat	Input	HIGH
IGN	Car ignition	Input	ON/OFF
BELTD	Driver belt	Input	LOW
BELTP	Passenger belt	Input	LOW
ALARM	Alarm going off	Output	LOW


Step 3 – Plan the Solution
1.	Monitor ignition status – IGN must be HIGH
2.	Check if driver is seated and the driver’s belt is fastened
3.	Check if passenger is seated and the driver’s belt is fastened.
4.	Alarm goes off if the above conditions are not met.

